      "content": "it's interesting you say it's \"widely regarded as inadequate\" though. do historians actually see the structure of the UN as fundamentally broken and outdated for the modern world, or is the criticism mostly just about the specific way certain countries use their vetoes? like is the whole idea of global governance being seen as a failure now?",
